# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Next.js 16.1.4 application using App Router.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` version 1.3.1 via npm
- Package added to dependencies in package.json
- Lock file (package-lock.json) updated accordingly

### 2. Code Changes
**Modified: `app/layout.tsx`**
- Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the `<body>` tag, placed after `<Analytics />`
- Follows the recommended pattern for Next.js 13.5+ with App Router

## Implementation Details
- **Next.js Version**: 16.1.4 (App Router)
- **Package Manager**: npm
- **Import Path**: `@vercel/speed-insights/next` (correct for App Router)
- **Component Placement**: Inside root layout's `<body>` tag, maintaining existing structure with Vercel Analytics

## Verification
✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
✅ TypeScript compilation passed
✅ All dependencies properly resolved
✅ Lock files updated (package-lock.json)
⚠️ Note: Pre-existing linting error in `components/analytics/PercentileChart.tsx` (unrelated to this change)

## Files Modified
- `app/layout.tsx` - Added SpeedInsights import and component
